id: pmc-1w1r
title: Zero-regression guarantee for pm-changelog enhancements
description: "All new flags (--section-by, --conventional, --contributors, --limit, --since-version, --changelog-json) are strictly additive and opt-in. With no new flags, every existing invocation (replace, --check, --stdout, --github-step-summary, --json) is byte-identical to published 2026.6.2. Verified by diffing a pristine baseline build against the new build across 9 modes on a real pm fixture (all PASS), exit-code contract preserved (check clean=0/dirty=1), help text additive-only, and an e2e CLI regression test pinned to a recorded baseline string. Every sibling package's release workflow depends on this."
